to the editor re election what election by michael yaki op ed sept 25 the problem of being ignored in presidential elections is not limited to california and new york in most elections more than half the states are ignored voters who do n't live in so called swing states are in effect bystanders in these quadrennial events there is a solution to this troublesome problem that would also eliminate the possibility that a candidate could enter the white house with an electoral vote majority while losing the popular vote as has happened twice an amendment to the united states constitution should replace the archaic electoral vote system with a direct vote only in this manner will citizens in all 50 states be able to take part fully in selecting our nation 's leaders lawrence r foster san ramon calif sept 25 2000

